1
00:00:09,009 --> 00:00:11,136
The Battle of Qi.

2
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:14,431
The winner of the 1-on-1 face-off is…

3
00:00:16,266 --> 00:00:17,684
Young Master Jiseon.

4
00:00:19,144 --> 00:00:20,687
YOUNG MASTER JISEON SURVIVES

5
00:00:28,362 --> 00:00:32,991
We agreed that Young Master
Jiseon's energy was more powerful.

6
00:00:33,075 --> 00:00:36,078
You both gave
very accurate readings, though.

7
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:38,247
Everything Young Master Jiseon said

8
00:00:38,330 --> 00:00:41,875
was more touching,
and that's why I voted for him.

9
00:00:41,959 --> 00:00:42,960
Thank you.

10
00:00:45,379 --> 00:00:47,381
-Experience gives you depth.
-Yes.

11
00:00:48,090 --> 00:00:50,384
I think I read Seulbi's fortune

12
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:52,386
just like I would for any other client.

13
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:56,056
As shamans,
we understood each other better,

14
00:00:56,139 --> 00:00:58,058
so I think she was a good opponent.

15
00:00:59,142 --> 00:01:01,979
I think Young Master Jiseon
gave a good reading.

16
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:04,564
The fact that I was eliminated

17
00:01:04,648 --> 00:01:06,483
is probably my fate too.

18
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:09,820
I'm proud of myself for coming this far.

19
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:11,363
So, I have no regrets.

20
00:01:14,575 --> 00:01:16,493
The next face-off is

21
00:01:17,286 --> 00:01:19,037
between Shaman Junghwa…

22
00:01:25,544 --> 00:01:27,421
…and Yoon Daeman.

23
00:01:28,797 --> 00:01:32,551
I heard Yoon Daeman also does
Gugak.

24
00:01:37,723 --> 00:01:40,183
I got into Gugak first,

25
00:01:40,267 --> 00:01:42,311
and then I became a shaman.

26
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:49,901
Guess which body parts
he had the surgeries on.

27
00:01:49,985 --> 00:01:53,280
I saw him walk in,
and he looked this big to me.

28
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:57,617
It just came to me naturally.
"Gastrectomy."

29
00:01:57,701 --> 00:02:02,247
Seo Minsu weighed 150 kg,
which is considered severely overweight.

30
00:02:02,331 --> 00:02:03,874
He had a gastrectomy.

31
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:04,958
Gosh.

32
00:02:06,293 --> 00:02:11,089
Look at the address
and guess what kind of place it is.

33
00:02:11,173 --> 00:02:14,760
When I tried to imagine this place,
I smelled a lot of incense.

34
00:02:14,843 --> 00:02:16,720
So, I wonder if it's a columbarium.

35
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:18,930
Wow.

36
00:02:19,014 --> 00:02:20,140
He's right.

37
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:24,895
He's not an ordinary guy.

38
00:02:30,317 --> 00:02:32,027
They both look flashy.

39
00:02:32,611 --> 00:02:34,404
They have the most colorful outfits.

40
00:02:35,947 --> 00:02:38,283
It's a match between the flashiest people.

41
00:02:40,202 --> 00:02:42,454
It's tradition versus tradition.

42
00:02:43,205 --> 00:02:46,833
SHAMAN JUNGHWA GOES FIRST
YOON DAEMAN GOES SECOND

43
00:02:52,589 --> 00:02:53,590
A shaman

44
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:58,845
can't do the job if they don't believe
that their deities are the best.

45
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:04,851
The fate for you to read
is the deceased's cause of death.

46
00:03:04,935 --> 00:03:08,689
The first word that came to my mind
was "firefighter."

47
00:03:10,399 --> 00:03:12,734
He couldn't breathe.

48
00:03:12,818 --> 00:03:16,071
He inhaled smoke or something
and suffocated to death.

49
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:19,825
Find students that go
to Seoul National University.

50
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:23,120
Number 3, Han Boyeong.
I think she got into SNU as well.

51
00:03:23,203 --> 00:03:25,414
She's got the patience
to sit and study for hours.

52
00:03:25,497 --> 00:03:27,874
She's got that grit, and she's determined.

53
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:30,460
- "To sit and study." Right.
- Yes, it's about endurance.

54
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:34,840
I believe I've got my own style,

55
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:36,967
and that I'm the best at what I do.

56
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:41,221
Shaman Junghwa was very good.

57
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:44,141
She has that invincible aura.

58
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:57,404
- Double fans.
- Wow.

59
00:03:57,487 --> 00:03:58,697
- She has 2 fans?
- Uh…

60
00:03:58,780 --> 00:03:59,948
Her fans are unusual.

61
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:04,703
-She's got such beautiful fans.
-They're pretty.

62
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:06,037
Nice fans.

63
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:26,850
The first thing my Granny spirit says is…

64
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:30,479
I'll just be honest.
I hope you don't get offended.

65
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:36,109
I don't see parents in your life.

66
00:04:36,193 --> 00:04:37,360
There are no parents.

67
00:04:37,444 --> 00:04:40,781
Your parents didn't raise you.
Your grandmother did.

68
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:45,452
HIS GRANDMOTHER TOOK CARE OF HIM
BECAUSE HIS FATHER HAD TO WORK

69
00:04:45,535 --> 00:04:47,954
- He was raised by his grandmother, yes.
- Yeah.

70
00:04:48,038 --> 00:04:51,249
Isn't there a grandma
who used to serve deities?

71
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,710
She was someone like us.

72
00:04:54,628 --> 00:04:55,796
That's right.

73
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:57,881
His great-grandmother was a shaman.

74
00:04:57,964 --> 00:04:58,965
His great-grandmother.

75
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:00,050
Oh…

76
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,343
HIS GREAT-GRANDMOTHER WAS A SHAMAN

77
00:05:03,595 --> 00:05:04,763
You're kind-hearted.

78
00:05:04,846 --> 00:05:06,640
You're a kind soul,

79
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:08,433
but you have fiery outbursts.

80
00:05:08,517 --> 00:05:09,768
You have a short fuse.

81
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:11,394
You have a short fuse.

82
00:05:13,021 --> 00:05:15,607
- "Short fuse."
- That's expert lingo.

83
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:17,818
So you could be smiling 1 second,

84
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:19,820
but if you suddenly
dislike that person, you'd go…

85
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:23,323
and turn your back on them.

86
00:05:24,282 --> 00:05:25,700
- She's swearing.
- She is.

87
00:05:27,619 --> 00:05:29,579
That's who you are.

88
00:05:30,664 --> 00:05:35,001
I told you I do spiritual divination
and tarot too, right?

89
00:05:35,085 --> 00:05:36,586
- Oh, really?
- She does what too?

90
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:37,879
- Tarot.
- Huh?

91
00:05:37,963 --> 00:05:40,340
- She does tarot reading too?
- Oh, unbelievable.

92
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,717
- Yes, I had no idea.
- She does tarot too.

93
00:05:42,801 --> 00:05:45,011
- She does tarot too?
- Oh.

94
00:05:45,095 --> 00:05:48,515
I brought my deck,
so I'll entertain you with it.

95
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:50,308
- Can I have a go?
- Yes.

96
00:05:51,726 --> 00:05:54,229
What a shaman thing to say.
"Entertain you."

97
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:09,411
I've never seen a tarot master
dressed like that.

98
00:06:24,092 --> 00:06:25,385
Santong sticks.

99
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,345
She's using santong sticks.

100
00:06:31,558 --> 00:06:34,561
They're called santong sticks.

101
00:06:34,644 --> 00:06:37,564
It's a fortune-telling method

102
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:39,733
the blind used to use.

103
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:41,443
DIVINATION USING MARKED STICKS

104
00:06:41,526 --> 00:06:42,861
She's multi-talented.

105
00:06:46,448 --> 00:06:50,285
She read my fortune
using various tools,

106
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:51,578
and that was pretty fun.

107
00:06:51,661 --> 00:06:53,371
Still, it was a competition,

108
00:06:53,455 --> 00:06:54,873
so it got me a little nervous.

109
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,627
She doesn't hesitate.

110
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:01,421
She does both tarot reading
and Hexagram Divination.

111
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:04,841
A whole package.

112
00:07:06,384 --> 00:07:07,719
Don't worry.

113
00:07:07,802 --> 00:07:11,931
I think starting this year,
things are looking up for you.

114
00:07:12,015 --> 00:07:15,226
You're likely to travel overseas too.

115
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:18,647
I see you traveling not just as a shaman,

116
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:20,273
but as a singer too.

117
00:07:20,357 --> 00:07:22,609
- Oh.
- Wow.

118
00:07:23,151 --> 00:07:25,570
- He's a great singer.
- She knows he sings.

119
00:07:25,654 --> 00:07:26,696
He's a great singer.

120
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:27,781
Don't worry too much.

121
00:07:27,864 --> 00:07:29,449
The latter half of the year
is looking good.

122
00:07:29,532 --> 00:07:30,533
The only problem is…

123
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:33,995
I see a death in the family.

124
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:36,122
Someone in your family will pass away.

125
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,501
Oh, no.

126
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:43,254
Things will get bad this year,
and they'll pass away next year.

127
00:07:43,338 --> 00:07:46,299
The heavens decide when someone dies,
so there's nothing we can do,

128
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:48,510
but you should brace yourself.

129
00:07:50,261 --> 00:07:51,513
Someone will pass away?

130
00:07:52,055 --> 00:07:53,556
Ah…

131
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:55,725
That's really scary.

132
00:07:55,809 --> 00:07:57,894
- Someone will pass away?
- Well…

133
00:07:57,977 --> 00:08:01,648
Now, I'm getting that
you've always been feeling frustrated.

134
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:02,732
Hmm…

135
00:08:02,816 --> 00:08:04,067
Things haven't been going
as well as you hoped.

136
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,151
Mm-hmm.

137
00:08:05,235 --> 00:08:08,530
It's like you've been missing
that 1 big breakthrough.

138
00:08:08,613 --> 00:08:10,156
- He didn't get a big breakthrough?
- Hmm.

139
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:11,866
Right. He was on Mr. Trot too.

140
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:12,992
That's right.

141
00:08:13,076 --> 00:08:14,744
FAILED TO MAKE THE MAIN ROUND OF MR. TROT

142
00:08:15,370 --> 00:08:16,955
Well, first of all,

143
00:08:17,914 --> 00:08:19,499
I grew up

144
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:23,253
in crushing poverty. I was so sick of it.

145
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:25,505
I lived with my grandmother.

146
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:26,881
Uh…

147
00:08:26,965 --> 00:08:29,926
We'd even eat food that had gone bad.

148
00:08:30,009 --> 00:08:33,805
We'd add baking soda
to make it safer to eat.

149
00:08:37,934 --> 00:08:39,227
Oh, dear…

150
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:42,731
Oh, my word.

151
00:08:42,814 --> 00:08:44,399
They were that poor.

152
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:48,611
I worked really hard to get into
a high school for the arts,

153
00:08:48,695 --> 00:08:51,573
but I had to drop out

154
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,700
because I couldn't afford the tuition.

155
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:56,745
The tuition at the time
was 900,000 won a month.

156
00:08:56,828 --> 00:08:58,913
That much every month…

157
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:01,583
-It was a lot to us.
-Yes.

158
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:03,752
- To me and my grandma.
- It still is a lot of money.

159
00:09:03,835 --> 00:09:07,422
So my father worked at construction sites,

160
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:10,800
but he got into an accident
that broke his spine.

161
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:13,303
He ended up
with a severe spinal disability.

162
00:09:13,386 --> 00:09:14,929
Oh, dear.

163
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:17,390
- That's terrible.
- So then…

164
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:22,771
I had to look after him,

165
00:09:22,854 --> 00:09:25,982
so I had no choice
but to drop out of high school.

166
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:29,152
I don't know why,
but the teachers were so mean back then.

167
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:31,696
They'd put up a list of kids
who didn't pay for school meals.

168
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:34,449
- Yes, they'd even read it out loud.
- Those who didn't pay tuition.

169
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:37,077
- Oh, no!
- Yeah, they did.

170
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,369
Yes, they did that.

171
00:09:39,746 --> 00:09:42,248
My name would be on all the lists.

172
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:45,251
Well, but I could endure that much.

173
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:52,008
But then a kid called me a beggar.
He said, "You darn beggar."

174
00:09:52,092 --> 00:09:53,968
Oh, that hurts.

175
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,513
Oh…

176
00:09:57,514 --> 00:09:59,349
As soon as I heard that…

177
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:02,102
Gosh, in that moment,

178
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:04,437
it felt like…

179
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:07,273
the world was crumbling down.

180
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:12,487
That's when I gave up on Gugak.

181
00:10:15,365 --> 00:10:16,574
You've been through a lot.

182
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:20,036
Everyone here has a sad story.

183
00:10:22,831 --> 00:10:24,958
I worked part-time instead.

184
00:10:26,417 --> 00:10:29,337
Then a friend I used to do pansori
with

185
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,880
called me up one day

186
00:10:30,964 --> 00:10:33,508
and said, "I'm learning
from an intangible heritage master."

187
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:35,260
"Come by the studio." So I went.

188
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:37,470
That master was so generous

189
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:39,806
and taught me for free.

190
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:42,433
He's blessed.

191
00:10:42,517 --> 00:10:43,935
He was blessed
with someone special.

192
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:46,229
What a blessing.

193
00:10:46,312 --> 00:10:48,606
That's when I started learning pansori.

194
00:10:49,357 --> 00:10:51,568
When I won prize money in a contest,

195
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:53,319
I gave it all to my teacher.

196
00:10:58,199 --> 00:10:59,200
That's admirable.

197
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:03,454
So, because my job isn't
a very stable one,

198
00:11:03,538 --> 00:11:06,916
I worry I'll end up in poverty again.

199
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,585
I'm afraid of poverty.

200
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:10,044
That could be a real concern.

201
00:11:10,879 --> 00:11:12,672
But you know,

202
00:11:12,755 --> 00:11:15,550
you're a very blessed person, Mr. Yoon.

203
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:18,636
You were given a way out each time.

204
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:21,014
That's how you were able to go to school

205
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:23,641
and learn how to sing.

206
00:11:23,725 --> 00:11:26,060
You couldn't have done any of that
without the deities' help,

207
00:11:26,144 --> 00:11:28,188
and of course, your own hard work too.

208
00:11:28,271 --> 00:11:32,483
- Things are looking up starting this year.
- Right.

209
00:11:32,567 --> 00:11:34,861
Prepare for that opportunity.

210
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:36,988
- Keep your energy up. Good luck.
- Okay.

211
00:11:39,115 --> 00:11:40,158
I think

212
00:11:40,909 --> 00:11:42,869
I've been lucky

213
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:46,998
to have good people help me
throughout my life.

214
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:50,084
While telling my story today,

215
00:11:50,168 --> 00:11:54,005
I was reminded of the people
I'm grateful to.

216
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:56,549
Now I feel like
I can take another step forward.

217
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:58,635
I feel more at ease.

218
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:02,055
He's got good people around him
because he's a good person.

219
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:06,684
Yoon Daeman,

220
00:12:06,768 --> 00:12:08,853
please begin your reading.

221
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:14,275
From what I've seen,
Mr. Yoon Daeman is…

222
00:12:14,359 --> 00:12:17,987
Well, every shaman has a special skill,
and he's extremely talented.

223
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:21,157
I was really excited
to see him giving a reading.

224
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:25,119
Your name, please.

225
00:12:25,203 --> 00:12:26,871
-My real name, not Shaman Junghwa?
-Yes.

226
00:12:26,955 --> 00:12:28,790
-It's Lee Minkyung.
-Lee Minkyung.

227
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:29,874
Yes.

228
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:45,181
Wow, his voice changed.

229
00:12:53,481 --> 00:12:55,108
He was chanting

230
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:57,986
like he was performing a rite,
not reading fortune.

231
00:12:58,069 --> 00:12:59,696
I was really surprised.

232
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:02,240
He sounds amazing.

233
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:13,042
Here is what my Granny spirit
is saying about you.

234
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:16,129
You are very lonely

235
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:18,256
and unable to stay with just 1 husband.

236
00:13:18,339 --> 00:13:20,883
You cannot stay with just 1 husband,

237
00:13:20,967 --> 00:13:23,136
and you end up shedding tears over men.

238
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:25,430
- Oh, wow.
- She's divorced.

239
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:26,514
2003, AGED 36
DIVORCED AFTER 7 YEARS OF MARRIAGE

240
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:27,682
- Ah…
- Oh…

241
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:30,518
And when you were in your 20s,

242
00:13:30,601 --> 00:13:33,980
you got lost and wandered.

243
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:36,524
There were so many
flashy people around you.

244
00:13:36,607 --> 00:13:38,109
…flashy people around you.

245
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:39,610
- In my 20s? Right.
- Yes.

246
00:13:40,570 --> 00:13:43,156
And before you became a shaman,

247
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:47,035
you had so many skills and talents.

248
00:13:47,118 --> 00:13:50,538
In arts or music,
if someone had given you a little push,

249
00:13:50,621 --> 00:13:53,166
you could have been quite successful.

250
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:56,419
But I'm getting
that you had no one offering help.

251
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:58,838
- Hmm.
- Goodness. She used to dance.

252
00:13:59,422 --> 00:14:01,007
- She was a dancer.
- Oh…

253
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:03,009
1981-83, AGED 14-16, MAJORED IN KOREAN
AND MODERN DANCE IN MIDDLE SCHOOL

254
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:12,727
They say you are financially comfortable.

255
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:15,730
Your relationships never come together.

256
00:14:15,813 --> 00:14:17,857
-You should never lend or borrow money.
-Right.

257
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:21,861
There are thieves and rats
with big eyes and big feet around you.

258
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:24,363
All sorts of thieves and rats.

259
00:14:24,447 --> 00:14:27,408
You give money easily,
but you struggle to get it back.

260
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:30,161
Wow.

261
00:14:30,745 --> 00:14:35,291
Do the deities keep talking,
telling you what to say?

262
00:14:37,794 --> 00:14:41,214
Before you became a shaman,
you must've had your own business.

263
00:14:41,297 --> 00:14:43,007
You can't work under other people.

264
00:14:43,091 --> 00:14:46,469
Let's see.
Perhaps, you sold drinks or something.

265
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:50,431
I'm being told
you were a great salesperson.

266
00:14:50,515 --> 00:14:51,724
Oh!

267
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:53,726
- Oh…
- She's run a lot of businesses.

268
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:57,105
A coffee shop and a Japanese bar.
Both sell drinks.

269
00:14:58,815 --> 00:14:59,982
What on earth?

270
00:15:00,066 --> 00:15:01,859
2008, AGED 41
TOOK OVER HER BROTHER'S CAFÉ

271
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:04,362
After you turned 40,

272
00:15:04,445 --> 00:15:07,073
you suffered lots of hardships.

273
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:10,118
Your business hit rock bottom.

274
00:15:10,201 --> 00:15:13,162
It was the worst time for you financially.

275
00:15:15,706 --> 00:15:17,500
She lost the security deposit.

276
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:21,712
2006, AGED 39, CLOSED BAR AFTER 2 YEARS,
LOST ALL OF SECURITY DEPOSIT

277
00:15:21,796 --> 00:15:24,507
And like I said, your family was cursed

278
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:26,342
because of issues with the graveyard.

279
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:29,554
There must've been back-to-back deaths.

280
00:15:29,637 --> 00:15:31,222
…back-to-back deaths.

281
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:34,976
- Oh. Wow…
- What? Where? Deaths?

282
00:15:36,102 --> 00:15:37,103
Ah…

283
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:39,188
- Oh, my. Her parents.
- Back-to-back deaths.

284
00:15:39,272 --> 00:15:40,940
FATHER DIED IN 2024, MOTHER DIED IN 2025

285
00:15:41,023 --> 00:15:42,692
- It's game over.
- Wow…

286
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:44,193
He's on a roll.

287
00:15:44,277 --> 00:15:45,945
That'll be all.

288
00:15:48,364 --> 00:15:50,491
Whoa. Wow…

289
00:15:51,742 --> 00:15:55,538
- He got so much right that I'm lost.
- Yes, me too.

290
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:59,000
It's like he laid out
her entire life story for us.

291
00:16:00,251 --> 00:16:02,670
They're certainly on another level.

292
00:16:02,753 --> 00:16:05,590
Wasn't it like watching the White Tiger
and the Azure Dragon fight?

293
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:06,966
That's how I felt.

294
00:16:07,842 --> 00:16:09,302
First of all,

295
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:13,472
although this show
is called Battle of Fates,

296
00:16:13,556 --> 00:16:15,850
it's not an actual battle, right?

297
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:18,102
But watching you guys compete

298
00:16:18,186 --> 00:16:21,147
reminded me of the movie
Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon.

299
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:23,816
Seriously.

300
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:26,110
- Yes, seriously.
- That's what I said.

301
00:16:26,194 --> 00:16:29,363
It was as if 2 martial arts masters

302
00:16:29,447 --> 00:16:31,407
were having a sword fight.

303
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:34,660
- It was so intense.
- With different types of swords.

304
00:16:34,744 --> 00:16:36,829
Before we say anything,

305
00:16:36,913 --> 00:16:38,748
- tell us what gave you the chills.
- Wow…

306
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:41,083
Things that made you wonder
how he found out.

307
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:44,378
- For me, it was the back-to-back deaths.
- Oh…

308
00:16:44,462 --> 00:16:46,714
I lost someone this year
and another last year.

309
00:16:47,924 --> 00:16:50,760
My father passed away of old age,

310
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:53,930
and my mother passed last week
of an illness.

311
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,098
- Oh…
- Yes.

312
00:16:57,141 --> 00:17:01,520
Oh, dear. She didn't even have
enough time to grieve properly.

313
00:17:01,604 --> 00:17:02,980
Ah…

314
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,275
Oh, dear. I see.

315
00:17:09,779 --> 00:17:12,031
He said that in your 20s,

316
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:14,116
there were
lots of flashy people around you.

317
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,576
Back then…

318
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:17,578
When I was in my 20s,

319
00:17:17,662 --> 00:17:19,497
I was young and pretty.

320
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:21,290
I think what he saw was me.

321
00:17:21,374 --> 00:17:23,960
Yes, I saw a vision.
You were pretty.

322
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:27,004
Good for you! You're awesome!

323
00:17:27,088 --> 00:17:28,839
She's a queen. A girlboss.

324
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,134
"Saw her in a vision," he said.

325
00:17:32,843 --> 00:17:36,389
It could be that
you were pretty and popular,

326
00:17:36,472 --> 00:17:39,433
but he said "flashy people,"
and I wondered what that meant.

327
00:17:42,937 --> 00:17:44,772
You went clubbing a lot.

328
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:47,817
-Yes, that's right.
-Yes, I saw flashing lights.

329
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,318
He's good.

330
00:17:49,402 --> 00:17:51,070
He was spot-on.

331
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:53,698
And when I went clubbing, I danced.

332
00:17:55,241 --> 00:17:59,704
Shaman Junghwa,
it says here you often went clubbing,

333
00:17:59,787 --> 00:18:02,498
and you think that was a symptom
of your shamanic illness.

334
00:18:02,582 --> 00:18:04,667
That was because

335
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,752
after I went to college,

336
00:18:06,836 --> 00:18:08,379
I started seeing things.

337
00:18:08,462 --> 00:18:12,883
But then I went to a club
with all the bright lights and loud music,

338
00:18:12,967 --> 00:18:14,844
and it put me in a trance.

339
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:17,221
For a moment, I could forget everything.

340
00:18:17,305 --> 00:18:19,098
That was a symptom
of my shamanic illness too.

341
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:20,349
I used to dance a lot

342
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:21,934
before becoming a shaman too.

343
00:18:22,018 --> 00:18:25,146
I loved that,
so I partied hard for about 2 years.

344
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:27,356
Two years?

345
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:30,484
Two years makes you a hardcore clubber.

346
00:18:30,568 --> 00:18:32,320
He was right
about your artistic talents.

347
00:18:33,863 --> 00:18:35,489
That's so funny.

348
00:18:37,325 --> 00:18:42,288
Fate Reapers.
Between Shaman Junghwa and Yoon Daeman,

349
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:45,625
choose the survivor.

350
00:18:48,377 --> 00:18:50,713
Gosh, this is so…

351
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:53,174
I just can't get used to this.

352
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:54,634
I can't watch.

353
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:57,720
It's a shame they went against each other.

354
00:18:57,803 --> 00:19:00,014
- They got so much right.
- Yes.

355
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:06,103
Honestly?
You want my honest take?

356
00:19:06,187 --> 00:19:09,065
Of course, I want to beat them all.
Are you kidding me?

357
00:19:10,191 --> 00:19:12,943
I'll keep going,
trusting in my deities.

358
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:20,242
- Oh, gosh. They voted.
- Oh, no.

359
00:19:20,326 --> 00:19:23,162
The winner of the 1-on-1 face-off is…

360
00:19:31,879 --> 00:19:34,131
Yoon Daeman.

361
00:19:34,215 --> 00:19:35,633
YOON DAEMAN SURVIVES

362
00:19:37,134 --> 00:19:38,552
-His energy was stronger.
-Yes.

363
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:40,429
- It was.
- Yeah.

364
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:43,182
Yoon Daeman, Shaman Junghwa,

365
00:19:43,265 --> 00:19:45,893
your match was actually incredibly close.

366
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:47,853
Yes. It was close.

367
00:19:47,937 --> 00:19:50,147
But Daeman got a lot more details

368
00:19:50,231 --> 00:19:53,359
that were accurate and to the point.

369
00:19:54,402 --> 00:19:57,488
Everyone here
is incredibly formidable,

370
00:19:57,571 --> 00:19:59,365
and I was chosen as the winner.

371
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:02,159
I'm really grateful for that.

372
00:20:02,785 --> 00:20:06,163
I could only say about a quarter
or a fifth of what I'd normally tell

373
00:20:06,247 --> 00:20:08,749
a client at my own shrine.

374
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:12,795
But I won't make excuses
because that was the limit of my skills.

375
00:20:13,462 --> 00:20:16,549
Even if I lost, I didn't want
to embarrass myself. That's what mattered.

376
00:20:17,425 --> 00:20:21,470
By the way, I loved the way Daeman sang
as his Granny spirit.

377
00:20:21,554 --> 00:20:24,098
♪ I think that's all I have to say ♪

378
00:20:24,181 --> 00:20:27,727
That was a terrible impression.

379
00:20:30,354 --> 00:20:32,314
The next face-off is…

380
00:20:33,983 --> 00:20:35,651
…between Lee Kookjoo

381
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:38,487
and Kim Baekmun.

382
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:40,656
He's so admirable.

383
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:42,241
He has over 30 years of experience.

384
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:43,868
Wow, for real?

385
00:20:48,289 --> 00:20:51,333
I can't beat his skills
that come from years of experience,

386
00:20:51,417 --> 00:20:53,377
but with my energy,

387
00:20:53,961 --> 00:20:55,504
maybe I can take control.

388
00:20:55,588 --> 00:20:58,257
To be honest,
I have lots of experience,

389
00:20:58,340 --> 00:20:59,508
so I'm confident.

390
00:21:00,426 --> 00:21:02,011
I got into foot reading

391
00:21:02,094 --> 00:21:04,472
because I wanted a unique skill of my own.

392
00:21:04,555 --> 00:21:05,681
It's quite unusual.

393
00:21:06,682 --> 00:21:08,142
I don't want to be ordinary.

394
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:11,937
You can tell someone's personality
or situation from their feet,

395
00:21:12,021 --> 00:21:13,814
and if you go even deeper,

396
00:21:13,898 --> 00:21:16,150
you can even read their thoughts.

397
00:21:17,318 --> 00:21:18,986
We have different genres now.

398
00:21:19,069 --> 00:21:20,321
Oh…

399
00:21:20,404 --> 00:21:23,115
A foot reader and a tarot master.

400
00:21:23,199 --> 00:21:24,200
Yes.

401
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:26,076
- This should be fun.
- Yeah.

402
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,703
How will he read her fortune?

403
00:21:27,787 --> 00:21:28,913
Wait a minute.

404
00:21:28,996 --> 00:21:31,165
- Will Kookjoo be showing him her feet?
- She has to.

405
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:34,210
My feet will air on Disney+?

406
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:36,295
My bare feet?

407
00:21:37,755 --> 00:21:38,839
No way!

408
00:21:40,633 --> 00:21:41,926
My gosh.

409
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:43,844
Which foot? Left or right?

410
00:21:43,928 --> 00:21:45,054
I need to see both.

411
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:47,223
I need to look at both for foot reading.

412
00:21:47,306 --> 00:21:48,349
Oh, geez.

413
00:21:49,183 --> 00:21:51,602
Because I have to show him my feet,

414
00:21:51,685 --> 00:21:55,356
I rubbed my Chanel lip balm
on my soles 4 hours ago.

415
00:21:58,317 --> 00:22:00,194
Rumor has it that you used 2 whole sticks.

416
00:22:00,277 --> 00:22:02,947
Yes,
but I left them in the dressing room.

417
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:04,949
I hope no one uses them on their lips.

418
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:09,662
She's worried about someone using them,
not about getting them stolen.

419
00:22:10,329 --> 00:22:11,705
Kookjoo's bare feet

420
00:22:11,789 --> 00:22:14,124
will be broadcast
in more than 150 countries.

421
00:22:14,208 --> 00:22:15,584
K-foot.

422
00:22:15,668 --> 00:22:17,628
It used to be just K-food.

423
00:22:17,711 --> 00:22:19,338
- It's not "food." It's "foot."
- Ah…

424
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:23,551
This will haunt her forever.

425
00:22:24,134 --> 00:22:25,302
Oh, no…

426
00:22:26,470 --> 00:22:29,390
Kim Baekmun goes first.
Please begin your reading.

427
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:32,560
Let's see your feet.

428
00:22:32,643 --> 00:22:34,186
He's holding something.

429
00:22:34,770 --> 00:22:35,980
A magnifying glass?

430
00:22:36,063 --> 00:22:37,523
It's a magnifying glass.

431
00:22:45,489 --> 00:22:48,826
No 2 people in the world
have the same feet.

432
00:22:50,369 --> 00:22:53,122
You won't find out anything
with a slight glance at the feet.

433
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:54,623
You must look closely.

434
00:22:57,501 --> 00:22:59,628
I've never seen anything like this.

435
00:22:59,712 --> 00:23:01,046
Same here.

436
00:23:01,130 --> 00:23:02,965
What kind of match is this?

437
00:23:03,048 --> 00:23:06,427
Well, Kookjoo.

438
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:08,137
I must say, you have very nice feet.

439
00:23:11,181 --> 00:23:14,226
There are calluses on the soles,
but you should be proud of them.

440
00:23:14,310 --> 00:23:15,311
Oh!

441
00:23:15,936 --> 00:23:17,980
Yes, it means she's worked hard.

442
00:23:23,444 --> 00:23:25,613
Her feet are bent backward.

443
00:23:25,696 --> 00:23:26,906
That means…

444
00:23:26,989 --> 00:23:28,824
She has itchy feet. The urge to travel.

445
00:23:28,908 --> 00:23:30,951
- I do.
- She needs to be

446
00:23:31,035 --> 00:23:33,370
moving around a lot to thrive.

447
00:23:33,454 --> 00:23:34,997
- She's never in 1 place.
- Oh…

448
00:23:35,080 --> 00:23:38,000
- She travels between Korea and Japan now.
- Yes.

449
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:40,794
2025, AGED 40, VISITS JAPAN OFTEN
FOR YOUTUBE CONTENT

450
00:23:40,878 --> 00:23:43,839
Even if it's not for work,
she's always on the move.

451
00:23:43,923 --> 00:23:45,132
Oh, really?

452
00:23:45,215 --> 00:23:47,801
- Your second toe is the biggest.
- Yes.

453
00:23:47,885 --> 00:23:49,178
-It's the longest.
-That means

454
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:52,598
- your mother has a strong presence.
- Yes.

455
00:23:52,681 --> 00:23:54,433
- She does.
- That's what it means.

456
00:23:54,516 --> 00:23:56,727
Her mom is a church deaconess.

457
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:58,270
She's a strong character.

458
00:23:58,354 --> 00:24:00,022
The second toe also means honor.

459
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:01,106
Okay.

460
00:24:01,774 --> 00:24:04,360
- You have strong leadership.
- Ah…

461
00:24:04,443 --> 00:24:06,403
Her second toe
is particularly long.

462
00:24:07,029 --> 00:24:09,073
You know
how to bring people together.

463
00:24:09,156 --> 00:24:10,574
Mmm.

464
00:24:10,658 --> 00:24:13,327
- You draw your juniors closer to you.
- Hmm.

465
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:15,537
If you move, people flock to you.

466
00:24:16,538 --> 00:24:19,166
You're a generous person,

467
00:24:19,249 --> 00:24:22,461
so your friends really like you.

468
00:24:23,253 --> 00:24:24,380
Oh…

469
00:24:24,964 --> 00:24:26,298
- Totally.
- Ah…

470
00:24:26,382 --> 00:24:28,217
- She always looks out for her juniors.
- Yes.

471
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,427
- He's good.
- Wow.

472
00:24:31,804 --> 00:24:33,472
The heels look good too.

473
00:24:33,555 --> 00:24:35,683
Wide and clean.

474
00:24:36,684 --> 00:24:39,395
That means good health
and comfortable latter years.

475
00:24:39,478 --> 00:24:40,479
Oh…

476
00:24:40,562 --> 00:24:42,272
- If you invest in real estate later,
-Yes?

477
00:24:42,856 --> 00:24:44,400
you could make good money from it.

478
00:24:44,483 --> 00:24:46,485
Oh!

479
00:24:46,568 --> 00:24:47,611
That's the best.

480
00:24:47,695 --> 00:24:49,655
She owns a building.

481
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:51,657
She does. I guess the price will go up.

482
00:24:52,157 --> 00:24:54,076
-Foot reading is so fascinating.
-I know.

483
00:24:54,159 --> 00:24:55,452
I'd love to try myself.

484
00:24:55,536 --> 00:24:56,578
He's good.

485
00:24:56,662 --> 00:24:58,122
I want mine read too.

486
00:25:00,290 --> 00:25:02,292
- I'd like him to read my feet.
- Yes.

487
00:25:02,376 --> 00:25:04,003
I'm curious.

488
00:25:04,086 --> 00:25:07,047
Now, I'll look
at your birth chart and explain in detail.

489
00:25:07,131 --> 00:25:08,132
Yes.

490
00:25:08,215 --> 00:25:10,217
This is the real deal.

491
00:25:10,884 --> 00:25:15,514
Kookjoo, yourbirth chart
shows a change of occupation.

492
00:25:15,597 --> 00:25:18,809
Between last year and this year.

493
00:25:18,892 --> 00:25:20,686
- And documents.
- Yes.

494
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:23,605
It looks like you tried to get one.

495
00:25:23,689 --> 00:25:25,691
A document?

496
00:25:25,774 --> 00:25:28,318
A document isn't just
a land deed or a house deed.

497
00:25:28,402 --> 00:25:30,237
- A contract is a document too.
- Right.

498
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:32,448
There seems to be
some sort of contract

499
00:25:32,531 --> 00:25:34,575
- that you hoped to get signed.
- Mmm.

500
00:25:34,658 --> 00:25:37,494
You really wanted it to go through.

501
00:25:37,578 --> 00:25:38,620
A document?

502
00:25:42,541 --> 00:25:43,917
Did she sign with a new agency?

503
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:48,172
- February or March this year.
- Yes.

504
00:25:48,255 --> 00:25:52,176
That's probably when you signed it
or almost did.

505
00:25:53,302 --> 00:25:54,553
You're right.

506
00:25:56,138 --> 00:25:57,765
She said, "You're right."

507
00:25:57,848 --> 00:26:00,225
- She said he's right?
- Yes, she did.

508
00:26:00,309 --> 00:26:01,310
Who did?

509
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:03,228
- Kookjoo.
- Oh, really?

510
00:26:03,312 --> 00:26:04,730
There must be something we don't know.

511
00:26:04,813 --> 00:26:05,814
The truth is,

512
00:26:05,898 --> 00:26:08,692
I'd signed a 10-year contract
with my previous agency,

513
00:26:09,276 --> 00:26:11,528
and it expired this March.

514
00:26:12,988 --> 00:26:14,198
