695
00:35:14,613 --> 00:35:17,282
She runs a company
and does tarot reading too.

696
00:35:17,365 --> 00:35:18,450
CORPORATE CONSULTANT, TAROT MASTER

697
00:35:18,533 --> 00:35:19,784
Oh! That's true.

698
00:35:19,868 --> 00:35:22,078
This is so accurate.

699
00:35:24,873 --> 00:35:27,125
This isn't actually my main job.

700
00:35:27,208 --> 00:35:28,376
Oh.

701
00:35:28,877 --> 00:35:30,879
I consider this

702
00:35:30,962 --> 00:35:33,882
more like a side hustle that could be big.

703
00:35:33,965 --> 00:35:36,926
I do this on the side of another job.

704
00:35:37,010 --> 00:35:38,928
Sobin's good.

705
00:35:39,554 --> 00:35:42,849
Do you have a dedicated space
for tarot reading?

706
00:35:43,642 --> 00:35:44,934
No, I don't.

707
00:35:45,477 --> 00:35:48,271
And I don't plan to open
a tarot reading shop.

708
00:35:48,355 --> 00:35:51,941
I'm being told you should open one
and put up a signboard.

709
00:35:52,025 --> 00:35:53,652
"Build a roof."

710
00:35:53,735 --> 00:35:56,655
Mmm. Maybe for something else
other than tarot.

711
00:35:57,197 --> 00:35:58,782
She's being defensive.

712
00:35:58,865 --> 00:36:01,117
- So there is something.
- She's getting defensive.

713
00:36:01,201 --> 00:36:03,912
They're like a spear and a shield.

714
00:36:03,995 --> 00:36:05,080
The tension is no joke.

715
00:36:06,956 --> 00:36:10,669
Also, I'm hearing
that you should use 2 names.

716
00:36:13,505 --> 00:36:15,382
You have 2 names,

717
00:36:15,465 --> 00:36:17,425
but you'll get another one.

718
00:36:17,509 --> 00:36:18,885
Mmm. Ooh…

719
00:36:18,968 --> 00:36:21,304
You have 2,
but you'll end up with 3.

720
00:36:21,388 --> 00:36:22,514
Nice.

721
00:36:24,182 --> 00:36:25,350
- "Nice"?
- Why?

722
00:36:25,433 --> 00:36:26,559
She's right?

723
00:36:26,643 --> 00:36:28,478
- For real?
- She has 3 names!

724
00:36:28,561 --> 00:36:30,105
- What?
- Wow, geez.

725
00:36:30,188 --> 00:36:32,649
She has 3 names.
It's not written in here, though.

726
00:36:32,732 --> 00:36:34,109
- No way.
- This is nuts.

727
00:36:35,819 --> 00:36:37,779
She's getting everything right.

728
00:36:38,571 --> 00:36:41,032
- Rumi looks flustered.
- She does.

729
00:36:41,116 --> 00:36:43,618
I'm getting that a lot has changed

730
00:36:43,702 --> 00:36:46,454
in the past 3 to 4 years.

731
00:36:48,665 --> 00:36:51,960
"The gossip has almost blown over.
Stick it out until next year."

732
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:54,421
- Next year?
- Beware of gossip until then.

733
00:36:54,504 --> 00:36:56,923
- "Beware," right.
- But it's a good thing.

734
00:36:57,006 --> 00:36:59,676
People are jealous
because they think highly of you.

735
00:36:59,759 --> 00:37:01,386
Don't let it get to you.

736
00:37:02,637 --> 00:37:04,639
They're jealous for a reason.

737
00:37:05,265 --> 00:37:07,517
- I try to think I'm just that cute.
- Yes, do that.

738
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:09,436
-Just think it's because you're beautiful.
-Right.

739
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:11,187
Just enjoy it. Who cares?

740
00:37:12,397 --> 00:37:15,400
People are jealous of you.
That's a good thing.

741
00:37:17,026 --> 00:37:20,822
People want to pluck a beautiful flower.

742
00:37:21,698 --> 00:37:24,159
That's how you should take it.

743
00:37:26,327 --> 00:37:29,205
The truth is,
I've spent the past 3 years

744
00:37:29,289 --> 00:37:33,126
trying to overcome myself.

745
00:37:33,209 --> 00:37:35,754
I struggled with social anxiety disorder

746
00:37:35,837 --> 00:37:38,131
for about a year and a half,

747
00:37:38,214 --> 00:37:41,217
and it took me about a year

748
00:37:41,301 --> 00:37:44,637
to a year and a half
to overcome the worst of it.

749
00:37:46,055 --> 00:37:49,225
So what she said really resonated with me,

750
00:37:49,309 --> 00:37:51,352
and I felt a mix of emotions.

751
00:37:52,479 --> 00:37:54,814
She gives such a comforting reading.

752
00:37:55,565 --> 00:37:57,066
She doesn't sound like a 26-year-old.

753
00:37:57,150 --> 00:37:58,860
- No.
- She sounds so mature.

754
00:37:58,943 --> 00:38:01,446
What I'm most curious about

755
00:38:01,529 --> 00:38:04,908
is the part where she talked about
you having 2 then 3 names.

756
00:38:04,991 --> 00:38:06,868
- There's nothing about that here.
- Right.

757
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:08,578
Do you have other names?

758
00:38:08,661 --> 00:38:10,997
- Yes, I do.
- What are they?

759
00:38:11,080 --> 00:38:13,082
- I have my Korean name, my real name.
- Yes.

760
00:38:13,166 --> 00:38:15,335
- Then there's Rumi.
- And?

761
00:38:15,418 --> 00:38:16,920
Then there's my English name.

762
00:38:18,379 --> 00:38:20,673
The reason I said, "Nice" when she said

763
00:38:20,757 --> 00:38:22,091
- I'd have a third name
-Yes?

764
00:38:22,175 --> 00:38:25,261
is because I came up with the name Rumi

765
00:38:25,345 --> 00:38:28,014
just for this show, as my stage name.

766
00:38:28,097 --> 00:38:29,599
- Oh.
- Wow.

767
00:38:30,642 --> 00:38:33,186
I wouldn't have been that surprised
if she'd said I had 3 names,

768
00:38:33,269 --> 00:38:35,814
but she said I had 2 but now I have 3.

769
00:38:35,897 --> 00:38:37,649
That's why I said, "Nice."

770
00:38:38,441 --> 00:38:41,861
Sobin, you saw those 3 names?

771
00:38:41,945 --> 00:38:44,864
Yes. I was told she mainly uses 2,

772
00:38:44,948 --> 00:38:46,783
-Right.
-but then I was told she has 3 names.

773
00:38:46,866 --> 00:38:48,535
- Rumi, her new name.
- Yes.

774
00:38:49,828 --> 00:38:50,829
Wow… She's good.

775
00:38:50,912 --> 00:38:52,038
She killed it.

776
00:38:52,622 --> 00:38:55,458
- She talks as if she looked it up online.
- Exactly.

777
00:38:56,251 --> 00:38:57,919
You can't even find this online.

778
00:38:58,837 --> 00:39:00,922
Can I say something?

779
00:39:01,005 --> 00:39:02,090
Oh. Yes, sure.

780
00:39:03,675 --> 00:39:07,428
Earlier on, Daeman told me

781
00:39:07,512 --> 00:39:10,098
I should date a foreigner.

782
00:39:13,309 --> 00:39:16,396
- Mr. Yoon. Will I ever get married?
- Yes?

783
00:39:17,146 --> 00:39:18,189
- Married?
- Yes.

784
00:39:18,273 --> 00:39:20,692
- If you ever do, I hope it's not a Korean.
- Why not?

785
00:39:20,775 --> 00:39:23,069
- You should marry a foreigner.
- Why?

786
00:39:23,152 --> 00:39:25,905
- I see a foreigner who speaks Korean well.
- Oh, why? No.

787
00:39:25,989 --> 00:39:27,282
No, that's not what I want.

788
00:39:28,032 --> 00:39:30,994
My late grandma also told me
to date a foreigner.

789
00:39:31,077 --> 00:39:34,414
Everyone tells me
to date a foreigner and not a Korean.

790
00:39:34,497 --> 00:39:38,001
But hearing that actually made me
not want to date a foreigner.

791
00:39:38,084 --> 00:39:40,086
I really want to know

792
00:39:40,169 --> 00:39:42,422
why people tell me to date a foreigner.

793
00:39:42,505 --> 00:39:44,048
Like I said, I see your home overseas.

794
00:39:44,132 --> 00:39:46,175
But I can buy it myself, with my money.

795
00:39:46,259 --> 00:39:48,428
But things will be
a lot easier with a foreigner.

796
00:39:48,511 --> 00:39:51,556
You'll be on the same wavelength,
he'll understand you better,

797
00:39:51,639 --> 00:39:53,266
and he won't disrupt your work.

798
00:39:53,349 --> 00:39:55,768
No, I decide my own destiny.

799
00:39:55,852 --> 00:39:57,103
You shape your own destiny.

800
00:39:57,186 --> 00:39:58,813
I can create it the way I want.

801
00:39:58,897 --> 00:40:01,900
Why ask a shaman if you won't listen?

802
00:40:03,776 --> 00:40:05,737
But I like Korean men.

803
00:40:06,321 --> 00:40:08,615
Oh, you should be with a bohemian!

804
00:40:08,698 --> 00:40:10,867
You should be with a bohemian!

805
00:40:10,950 --> 00:40:11,951
A bohemian?

806
00:40:15,163 --> 00:40:17,040
Find yourself a bohemian.

807
00:40:17,123 --> 00:40:19,834
- With a big beard. Maybe a photographer.
- Oh, no.

808
00:40:19,918 --> 00:40:22,295
Someone who plays the violin and stuff.

809
00:40:22,378 --> 00:40:23,713
I don't like beards.

810
00:40:23,796 --> 00:40:25,465
Fine. Forget it then.

811
00:40:27,383 --> 00:40:28,593
Date whoever you want.

812
00:40:28,676 --> 00:40:31,179
Koreans have good skin

813
00:40:31,262 --> 00:40:32,889
and not much hair.

814
00:40:32,972 --> 00:40:35,934
- I just personally prefer Korean men.
- Koreans?

815
00:40:36,017 --> 00:40:37,352
Just go with the flow.

816
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:39,145
Marry whoever you love.

817
00:40:39,228 --> 00:40:42,231
I think I should find someone
who'd marry me first.

818
00:40:42,315 --> 00:40:45,777
Oh, gosh. If you get a client like her,
you should pretend you're off for the day.

819
00:40:49,614 --> 00:40:52,992
Rumi, please begin your reading.

820
00:40:53,076 --> 00:40:54,577
I wonder what she'll say.

821
00:40:54,661 --> 00:40:57,288
I wonder what Rumi's reading
is going to be like.

822
00:40:58,790 --> 00:41:00,458
- What's your real name?
- It's Lee Kieun.

823
00:41:00,541 --> 00:41:03,419
-"Lee Kieun"?
-Kieun. Ends with an N.

824
00:41:07,256 --> 00:41:10,218
When I hear someone's name,

825
00:41:10,301 --> 00:41:12,762
sometimes I feel or see something.

826
00:41:12,845 --> 00:41:15,139
If I do, I speak on it right away.

827
00:41:15,223 --> 00:41:18,977
If I can't make a good connection,

828
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:21,604
then I pick out a few cards.

829
00:41:22,188 --> 00:41:25,483
Today, I relied on my spirit
without using the cards.

830
00:41:32,991 --> 00:41:34,534
Uh…

831
00:41:35,159 --> 00:41:38,413
Let me ask you something just to see

832
00:41:38,496 --> 00:41:40,164
if I'm on the right frequency.

833
00:41:40,248 --> 00:41:42,375
"Frequency"?

834
00:41:42,875 --> 00:41:45,962
The reason you became a shaman…

835
00:41:46,045 --> 00:41:47,797
Does it go back

836
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:50,466
to when you were really young?

837
00:41:50,550 --> 00:41:53,094
When you were like 3 or 5 years old?

838
00:41:54,220 --> 00:41:56,639
Three or five years old?

839
00:41:56,723 --> 00:41:57,849
That's right, yes.

840
00:42:00,351 --> 00:42:03,104
That's when you started
to feel the spirits?

841
00:42:03,187 --> 00:42:04,397
That's when she had a shamanic illness.

842
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:07,316
2002-2005, AGED 3-6, SHAMANIC ILLNESS
MADE HER SHAKE A SCARF AND JUMP

843
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:09,986
I suffered
from the shamanic illness when I was 3

844
00:42:10,069 --> 00:42:11,863
and started to act weird.

845
00:42:11,946 --> 00:42:15,450
It's very true that
everything started when I was 3.

846
00:42:17,243 --> 00:42:19,537
- Your relationship with your mom.
- Yes.

847
00:42:19,620 --> 00:42:22,707
It doesn't seem to be that great.

848
00:42:22,790 --> 00:42:24,375
Oh, really?

849
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:27,503
- Does my mom hate me?
- Huh?

850
00:42:27,587 --> 00:42:29,172
Does she hate me?

851
00:42:30,506 --> 00:42:32,175
- She's so cute.
- What a cute reaction.

852
00:42:33,051 --> 00:42:35,011
No, it's not that.

853
00:42:35,094 --> 00:42:38,097
You might get along fine,

854
00:42:38,181 --> 00:42:40,600
but your emotional connection

855
00:42:40,683 --> 00:42:43,061
seems a little off.

856
00:42:45,354 --> 00:42:49,275
Another keyword that came to my mind

857
00:42:49,358 --> 00:42:50,777
-was "sacrifice."
-Mmm. Okay.

858
00:42:50,860 --> 00:42:53,029
I'm being cautious when I say this,

859
00:42:53,112 --> 00:42:55,782
but the word "sacrifice" appeared to me.

860
00:42:57,992 --> 00:42:59,285
- She's right.
- Yes, it's true.

861
00:42:59,368 --> 00:43:00,828
She paid off debt.

862
00:43:00,912 --> 00:43:02,455
She paid off her parents' debt.

863
00:43:02,538 --> 00:43:04,457
2014, AGED 15, PAID OFF HER PARENTS'
1-BILLION-WON DEBT

864
00:43:04,540 --> 00:43:05,583
Hmm. Oh! That's crazy.

865
00:43:06,501 --> 00:43:09,295
I have a question for Sobin.

866
00:43:09,378 --> 00:43:10,546
Rumi said

867
00:43:10,630 --> 00:43:14,801
your relationship with your mother

868
00:43:14,884 --> 00:43:16,594
- didn't seem great.
- Yes.

869
00:43:16,677 --> 00:43:18,763
Do you have anything to say about that?

870
00:43:19,388 --> 00:43:22,225
My mom and I are very close.

871
00:43:22,725 --> 00:43:24,018
Because to me…

872
00:43:33,069 --> 00:43:34,237
Why cry if they're close?

873
00:43:41,452 --> 00:43:43,913
My mom and dad are my only friends.

874
00:43:43,996 --> 00:43:45,456
Oh, dear.

875
00:43:45,540 --> 00:43:47,333
Oh, gosh.

876
00:43:47,416 --> 00:43:48,584
Oh, no.

877
00:43:49,669 --> 00:43:51,754
- Oh, sweetie.
- Aw.

878
00:43:55,299 --> 00:43:58,094
Don't cry. I feel like I made you cry.

879
00:44:01,264 --> 00:44:03,141
Can I have a moment? Sorry.

880
00:44:05,017 --> 00:44:06,978
The reason why we clash

881
00:44:07,061 --> 00:44:08,688
is because of our deities.

882
00:44:08,771 --> 00:44:10,189
They don't get along well.

883
00:44:10,273 --> 00:44:12,233
My mom's family has some strong deities,

884
00:44:12,316 --> 00:44:14,402
and so does my dad's family.

885
00:44:14,485 --> 00:44:18,281
My main Guardian spirit
is my paternal grandmother,

886
00:44:18,364 --> 00:44:21,159
and that's why we clash.

887
00:44:21,742 --> 00:44:22,743
Seriously?

888
00:44:23,244 --> 00:44:24,662
Deities get into fights too.

889
00:44:25,371 --> 00:44:27,123
Her mom also has…

890
00:44:27,206 --> 00:44:29,417
- Between shamans…
- …shamanic lineage.

891
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:32,253
-As humans, they get along well.
-But the deities fight.

892
00:44:32,336 --> 00:44:34,130
They're fine, but their deities are not.

893
00:44:35,131 --> 00:44:37,216
And so…

894
00:44:37,300 --> 00:44:40,428
I was really surprised
when you mentioned it

895
00:44:40,511 --> 00:44:42,847
because I've had a really hard time

896
00:44:42,930 --> 00:44:45,474
over the past 3 years
because of the deities' fight.

897
00:44:45,558 --> 00:44:48,936
So I'm trying to work things out.

898
00:44:56,944 --> 00:45:01,908
Rumi said she saw the word "sacrifice."

899
00:45:01,991 --> 00:45:04,076
Does it make sense to you?

900
00:45:04,160 --> 00:45:07,830
I guess it makes sense in a few ways.

901
00:45:07,914 --> 00:45:11,334
First, I sacrifice myself for the deities.

902
00:45:27,016 --> 00:45:30,770
I've never lived my life
as an ordinary human being.

903
00:45:31,270 --> 00:45:33,481
I've never had friends my age.

904
00:45:33,564 --> 00:45:36,234
I didn't go to school,
so I've never gone on school trips either.

905
00:45:36,317 --> 00:45:38,527
I must keep all the strict rules,

906
00:45:38,611 --> 00:45:40,446
so you could say
it's a sacrifice of sorts.

907
00:45:41,239 --> 00:45:42,406
Second,

908
00:45:43,074 --> 00:45:44,951
I think everyone here can relate to this.

909
00:45:45,034 --> 00:45:46,827
People like us

910
00:45:47,495 --> 00:45:49,205
have so many people to look after.

911
00:45:49,288 --> 00:45:51,082
Your family, your people.

912
00:45:51,165 --> 00:45:53,167
There are so many to care for.

913
00:45:53,251 --> 00:45:56,337
You could say
I sacrifice myself for them too.

914
00:45:58,798 --> 00:46:00,925
According to the book,

915
00:46:01,008 --> 00:46:04,053
you paid off your parents' debt.

916
00:46:04,136 --> 00:46:06,597
That could be a sacrifice too.

917
00:46:06,681 --> 00:46:07,974
Could you tell us about that?

918
00:46:08,557 --> 00:46:09,558
Wow.

919
00:46:10,142 --> 00:46:11,978
That's a bit complicated.

920
00:46:12,061 --> 00:46:14,522
My parents went into debt

921
00:46:14,605 --> 00:46:18,109
because they were punished
for having rites to prevent me

922
00:46:18,192 --> 00:46:19,986
from becoming a shaman.

923
00:46:20,069 --> 00:46:22,071
And they had to pay for the rites too.

924
00:46:27,118 --> 00:46:29,078
It cost them a fortune.

925
00:46:29,161 --> 00:46:31,580
They spent billions of won.

926
00:46:31,664 --> 00:46:33,749
Oh, dear.

927
00:46:34,625 --> 00:46:36,752
Oh, does it cost that much?

928
00:46:36,836 --> 00:46:39,088
- Yes, because they did multiple rites.
- Oh…

929
00:46:39,171 --> 00:46:43,175
The reason why
I became a shaman when I was 7

930
00:46:43,259 --> 00:46:44,885
was because they thought I might die.

931
00:46:44,969 --> 00:46:46,554
- Oh, my word.
- Oh.

932
00:46:47,805 --> 00:46:48,806
Well…

933
00:46:48,889 --> 00:46:52,101
The doctor who delivered me,

934
00:46:52,184 --> 00:46:56,314
the monks, shamans, everyone…

935
00:46:56,397 --> 00:46:59,066
They told my mom I'd never live
past 7 years old.

936
00:46:59,150 --> 00:47:00,651
Oh…

937
00:47:01,444 --> 00:47:02,570
Geez.

938
00:47:02,653 --> 00:47:04,905
I can't imagine how you'd feel
to hear that.

939
00:47:06,824 --> 00:47:09,785
My mom was so scared to hear
I wouldn't live past 7 years old.

940
00:47:10,578 --> 00:47:12,872
And people kept telling her
the same thing.

941
00:47:12,955 --> 00:47:15,499
Even when I was 7, they said,
"She won't survive the year."

942
00:47:15,583 --> 00:47:17,543
"She won't see the new year."

943
00:47:19,795 --> 00:47:21,756
We say the deities "strike" you.

944
00:47:21,839 --> 00:47:24,633
They had so many rites performed
to keep the deities away,

945
00:47:24,717 --> 00:47:26,302
but I kept getting sick.

946
00:47:26,385 --> 00:47:29,555
Every business failed,
and they lost money.

947
00:47:29,638 --> 00:47:32,391
They went through so many hardships.

948
00:47:32,475 --> 00:47:34,226
They had to make a choice in the end,

949
00:47:34,310 --> 00:47:37,813
and I became a shaman before I knew it.

950
00:47:37,897 --> 00:47:40,358
It must've been heartbreaking
for my parents.

951
00:47:41,317 --> 00:47:44,612
To make their 7-year-old girl
become a shaman.

952
00:47:46,280 --> 00:47:48,324
They had many rites performed for me

953
00:47:48,407 --> 00:47:51,410
all the way up until I became a shaman.

954
00:47:51,494 --> 00:47:53,204
They went into debt because of it,

955
00:47:53,287 --> 00:47:55,164
and I paid it off

956
00:47:55,247 --> 00:47:57,875
by doing my work as a shaman.

957
00:48:00,044 --> 00:48:01,128
Oh, my days.

958
00:48:02,129 --> 00:48:05,049
Oh, she's so impressive
for someone so young.

959
00:48:05,674 --> 00:48:08,761
Oh… She was born in 2000.
She's just a child.

960
00:48:14,392 --> 00:48:16,727
Sobin became a shaman at a young age,

961
00:48:16,811 --> 00:48:18,229
and so did I.

962
00:48:18,813 --> 00:48:22,775
We didn't become shamans
because we wanted to.

963
00:48:22,858 --> 00:48:24,610
So I could relate to her a lot.

964
00:48:25,361 --> 00:48:27,655
Sobin's so genuine.

965
00:48:29,949 --> 00:48:33,035
Of course,
I want to have fun. I'm just 18.

966
00:48:34,120 --> 00:48:36,455
I was told, "While other kids
go to school with backpacks,

967
00:48:36,539 --> 00:48:38,457
you must stand on jakdu.
That's your fate."

968
00:48:38,541 --> 00:48:40,543
I feel great!

969
00:48:41,252 --> 00:48:44,296
"Also, while other kids play soccer,

970
00:48:44,380 --> 00:48:46,173
you must go praying."

971
00:48:46,257 --> 00:48:49,051
That's the destiny I was born with.

972
00:48:49,135 --> 00:48:50,511
Literally, it's my fate.

973
00:48:52,304 --> 00:48:53,889
We share the same fate.

974
00:48:53,973 --> 00:48:56,392
We've all lived rough lives,
and we're now shamans.

975
00:48:56,475 --> 00:48:58,310
So, I felt bad for her.

976
00:49:00,479 --> 00:49:02,189
All shamans have heartbreaking stories.

977
00:49:02,273 --> 00:49:03,274
Right.

978
00:49:04,984 --> 00:49:06,152
Fate Reapers.

979
00:49:06,652 --> 00:49:08,821
Between Lee Sobin and Rumi,

980
00:49:08,904 --> 00:49:11,574
choose the survivor.

981
00:49:11,657 --> 00:49:13,909
She did so well. She got everything right.

982
00:49:13,993 --> 00:49:16,620
- Sobin? Yes, she did.
- Moving abroad and the 3 names.

983
00:49:19,498 --> 00:49:21,584
But I think Rumi's pretty good too.

984
00:49:21,667 --> 00:49:22,793
- She is.
- I agree.

985
00:49:22,877 --> 00:49:25,087
It was more like spiritual divination
than tarot reading.

986
00:49:28,382 --> 00:49:29,842
This is so hard.

987
00:49:32,386 --> 00:49:33,762
Who should I vote for?

988
00:49:39,018 --> 00:49:40,644
- My gosh.
- I hate this part.

989
00:49:40,728 --> 00:49:43,272
- I can't watch.
- I hate this.

990
00:49:43,355 --> 00:49:44,857
The Battle of Qi.

991
00:49:46,192 --> 00:49:48,527
The winner of the 1-on-1 face-off is…

992
00:49:49,069 --> 00:49:50,362
The winner is?

993
00:49:55,534 --> 00:49:56,535
LEE SOBIN

994
00:49:57,786 --> 00:49:59,288
LEE SOBIN

995
00:49:59,371 --> 00:50:01,499
LEE SOBIN

996
00:50:01,582 --> 00:50:02,583
- Oh…
- …Lee Sobin.

997
00:50:05,169 --> 00:50:07,796
LEE SOBIN SURVIVES

998
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:10,883
Rumi, I hope you don't take
the 5–0 result at face value.

999
00:50:10,966 --> 00:50:13,385
We had a fierce discussion.

1000
00:50:13,469 --> 00:50:17,681
It's just that Sobin got more facts right.

1001
00:50:17,765 --> 00:50:19,892
That was the deciding factor
for our decision.

1002
00:50:19,975 --> 00:50:20,976
It was so hard.

1003
00:50:21,060 --> 00:50:22,728
- Honestly.
- It was a real tough one.

1004
00:50:23,312 --> 00:50:24,897
- Well done.
- Congratulations!

1005
00:50:26,690 --> 00:50:30,236
I experienced something
I never had before,

1006
00:50:30,319 --> 00:50:33,531
and I got to see other people
do their readings too.

1007
00:50:33,614 --> 00:50:35,783
This has been
a very meaningful experience.

1008
00:50:35,866 --> 00:50:39,036
I don't know why,
but I feel like I'll be back.

1009
00:50:40,204 --> 00:50:41,497
The survivors of the Battle of Qi are

1010
00:50:41,580 --> 00:50:42,831
Young Master Jiseon,

1011
00:50:42,915 --> 00:50:43,958
Pie,

1012
00:50:44,041 --> 00:50:45,251
Lady Wish,

1013
00:50:45,334 --> 00:50:46,335
Seolhwa,

1014
00:50:46,418 --> 00:50:47,920
Manshin Kwon Sujin,

1015
00:50:48,003 --> 00:50:49,129
Choi Hannah,

1016
00:50:49,213 --> 00:50:50,297
Lee Sobin,

1017
00:50:50,381 --> 00:50:51,507
Kim Baekmun,

1018
00:50:51,590 --> 00:50:52,758
Yoon Daeman,

1019
00:50:52,841 --> 00:50:53,968
and Monad.

1020
00:50:54,051 --> 00:50:55,135
Ten people in total.

1021
00:50:55,219 --> 00:50:56,554
THE 10 SURVIVORS OF BATTLE OF QI

1022
00:51:13,362 --> 00:51:15,781
What is it now?

1023
00:51:15,864 --> 00:51:18,158
What's this? There are stairs now.

1024
00:51:19,535 --> 00:51:21,495
Wow.

1025
00:51:21,579 --> 00:51:23,622
- What's this?
- What's going on here?

1026
00:51:25,749 --> 00:51:28,085
Welcome!

1027
00:51:28,669 --> 00:51:30,588
- Y'all are impressive.
- Congratulations!

1028
00:51:31,797 --> 00:51:32,923
The top 10.

1029
00:51:33,007 --> 00:51:35,926
- Hello.
- Welcome.

1030
00:51:36,427 --> 00:51:39,221
- What's this?
- They got here before we did.

1031
00:51:42,766 --> 00:51:44,810
We have a nice mix of contestants.

1032
00:51:51,358 --> 00:51:52,526
What could it be?

1033
00:51:56,238 --> 00:51:59,867
A survival game
where those who read fate bet their own.

1034
00:52:00,367 --> 00:52:02,286
Battle of Fates.

1035
00:52:02,911 --> 00:52:04,663
The third round is…

1036
00:52:12,713 --> 00:52:14,465
the Battle of Synergy.

1037
00:52:14,548 --> 00:52:16,300
THE BATTLE OF SYNERGY

1038
00:52:16,383 --> 00:52:17,801
What's that?

1039
00:52:19,011 --> 00:52:20,262
What is it about?

1040
00:52:20,929 --> 00:52:22,681
What are we supposed to do?

1041
00:52:25,017 --> 00:52:26,185
Gathered here are

1042
00:52:27,144 --> 00:52:28,437
shamans,

1043
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:29,772
saju experts,

1044
00:52:29,855 --> 00:52:31,190
tarot masters,

1045
00:52:31,774 --> 00:52:32,775
and foot readers, and so on.

1046
00:52:33,484 --> 00:52:37,112
Fate Readers with different backgrounds.

1047
00:52:37,946 --> 00:52:39,865
What kind of marvelous things will unfold

1048
00:52:40,658 --> 00:52:44,119
when they're brought together?

1049
00:52:44,787 --> 00:52:46,664
We'd like you to form teams

1050
00:52:47,373 --> 00:52:51,210
to test how well the Fate Readers
work together.

1051
00:52:51,293 --> 00:52:52,670
Oh!

1052
00:52:52,753 --> 00:52:54,213
It's a team battle.

1053
00:52:54,296 --> 00:52:58,676
Oh, I knew it. A team round.

1054
00:52:58,759 --> 00:53:01,637
I've seen team missions
on other survival shows,

1055
00:53:01,720 --> 00:53:04,556
-but I can't tell how this will go.
-I know.

1056
00:53:04,640 --> 00:53:06,600
- It's for K-pop idols, rappers.
- Yes.

1057
00:53:07,142 --> 00:53:08,811
Or dancers.

1058
00:53:08,894 --> 00:53:11,563
Everyone here works on their own.

1059
00:53:12,064 --> 00:53:14,274
Isn't this the first-ever
shamanism team battle?

1060
00:53:15,067 --> 00:53:16,527
Here it comes.

1061
00:53:18,362 --> 00:53:22,366
I've never read anyone's fortune
as part of a team.

1062
00:53:22,449 --> 00:53:23,784
It won't be easy.

1063
00:53:23,867 --> 00:53:25,828
We're all so different from each other.

1064
00:53:25,911 --> 00:53:27,246
I thought we'd clash.

1065
00:53:27,329 --> 00:53:28,956
If cracks form in the team,

1066
00:53:29,039 --> 00:53:30,874
it doesn't matter how good you are.

1067
00:53:30,958 --> 00:53:33,460
The deities won't connect
if they're angry.

1068
00:53:34,253 --> 00:53:36,714
We're good,
and the others must be just as good.

1069
00:53:36,797 --> 00:53:40,175
Then the energy might clash
and it could get messy.

1070
00:53:40,259 --> 00:53:43,178
So I was a bit worried.

1071
00:53:47,599 --> 00:53:49,268
Finally, the team battle
I was waiting for.

1072
00:53:49,768 --> 00:53:52,271
I'm a huge fan of survival shows,

1073
00:53:52,896 --> 00:53:54,565
and I absolutely love team battles.

1074
00:53:55,149 --> 00:53:56,233
So I was thrilled.

1075
00:53:58,360 --> 00:54:00,112
For the Battle of Synergy,

1076
00:54:00,863 --> 00:54:02,948
you will form teams of 3.

1077
00:54:03,031 --> 00:54:07,703
There will be a total of 4 teams.

1078
00:54:08,662 --> 00:54:09,747
Teams of 3?

1079
00:54:13,083 --> 00:54:14,710
-Teams of 3.
-Yes.

1080
00:54:14,793 --> 00:54:19,339
One, two, three.

1081
00:54:19,423 --> 00:54:21,508
We need 12 people,
but there are only 10.

1082
00:54:23,469 --> 00:54:24,678
Do we have more people coming?

1083
00:54:25,262 --> 00:54:27,639
Was there a consolation match?

1084
00:54:27,723 --> 00:54:29,892
To form teams of 3,
they need 2 more people.

1085
00:54:29,975 --> 00:54:32,060
-They're short 2 people.
-Yes.

1086
00:54:32,144 --> 00:54:33,479
Yes, there are only 10 of them.

1087
00:54:37,065 --> 00:54:39,735
For the Battle of Synergy,

1088
00:54:40,402 --> 00:54:43,697
2 Revived Fate Readers will join you.

1089
00:54:44,615 --> 00:54:46,450
I knew it.

1090
00:54:46,533 --> 00:54:48,535
So there are more people coming.

1091
00:54:49,578 --> 00:54:51,580
It meant there were more competitors,

1092
00:54:51,663 --> 00:54:53,916
so I thought things might get

1093
00:54:53,999 --> 00:54:56,627
even more heated.

1094
00:54:57,211 --> 00:54:58,378
Oh, who's coming?

1095
00:54:59,046 --> 00:55:00,964
Who could it be?
I wonder who made it.

1096
00:55:01,882 --> 00:55:03,300
AFTER THE BATTLE OF QI

1097
00:55:03,383 --> 00:55:05,886
Out of the 10
who got eliminated today,

1098
00:55:05,969 --> 00:55:09,306
-Yes.
-2 people can move on to the next round.

1099
00:55:09,389 --> 00:55:10,599
There were too many close matches.

1100
00:55:10,682 --> 00:55:12,351
They didn't deserve
to be eliminated.

1101
00:55:12,434 --> 00:55:14,394
- It was a huge shame.
- Yes.

1102
00:55:14,478 --> 00:55:17,105
- I want this person to move on.
- Yes.

1103
00:55:17,189 --> 00:55:19,483
- They are very competent.
- Okay.

1104
00:55:19,566 --> 00:55:21,568
- Let's go with these 2 people.
- Sounds good.

1105
00:55:21,652 --> 00:55:24,363
-Then we'll advance these 2 people.
-Okay.

1106
00:55:24,446 --> 00:55:25,489
Sounds good.

1107
00:55:26,240 --> 00:55:28,492
I wonder what face they'll make
when they walk in.

1108
00:55:31,495 --> 00:55:32,704
Why am I so nervous?

1109
00:55:34,373 --> 00:55:36,959
The first Revived Fate Reader.

1110
00:55:37,543 --> 00:55:38,627
- Come on out.
- From where?

1111
00:55:38,710 --> 00:55:40,212
Where are they coming out from?

1112
00:55:42,798 --> 00:55:44,174
- From where?
- Who is it?

1113
00:55:44,925 --> 00:55:47,261
- What's going on? Who is it?
- What? Who?

1114
00:55:48,887 --> 00:55:49,888
Who is it?

1115
00:55:50,472 --> 00:55:51,473
I can't see.

1116
00:55:58,438 --> 00:55:59,606
A fan?

1117
00:56:08,699 --> 00:56:09,825
Hello.

1118
00:56:11,451 --> 00:56:12,578
Hi, guys.

1119
00:56:12,661 --> 00:56:13,745
YOUNG MASTER PLUM BLOSSOM

1120
00:56:13,829 --> 00:56:17,666
To be honest,
I found him the most impressive.

1121
00:56:17,749 --> 00:56:19,876
It was close. I felt bad to see him go.

1122
00:56:19,960 --> 00:56:22,129
THE BATTLE OF QI
LADY WISH VS YOUNG MASTER PLUM BLOSSOM

1123
00:56:22,212 --> 00:56:25,257
The people around you
don't stick around for long.

1124
00:56:25,340 --> 00:56:28,802
People tend to come and go in your life
in 5-7 year cycles.

1125
00:56:29,553 --> 00:56:32,347
- She got divorced after about 5 years.
- Right.

1126
00:56:32,431 --> 00:56:34,641
-The ties didn't last.
-They were short-lived.

1127
00:56:34,725 --> 00:56:37,978
Physical work just isn't your strength.

1128
00:56:39,313 --> 00:56:41,732
That must be why
she ended up quitting sports.

1129
00:56:41,815 --> 00:56:43,150
You're right.

1130
00:56:43,233 --> 00:56:45,152
- Her shoulder.
- That's why.

1131
00:56:45,235 --> 00:56:49,531
Young Master Plum Blossom is
the shaman everyone's avoiding right now.

1132
00:56:50,032 --> 00:56:52,784
- It's Young Master Plum Blossom.
- Hello.

1133
00:56:52,868 --> 00:56:55,037
It's so good to see you again.

1134
00:56:55,120 --> 00:56:56,997
What the heck?
You said you were going home!

1135
00:56:57,873 --> 00:57:00,584
I knew you'd come back.
I knew it.

1136
00:57:00,667 --> 00:57:02,878
I loved it. Finally, a pretty face.

1137
00:57:05,422 --> 00:57:06,632
I was so happy to see him.

1138
00:57:06,715 --> 00:57:08,967
We went up against each other,

1139
00:57:09,051 --> 00:57:12,596
and I thought he'd do well
if he were given another chance.

1140
00:57:12,679 --> 00:57:15,891
I've basically come back from the dead.

1141
00:57:15,974 --> 00:57:18,352
I'll show them
everything I can do this time.

1142
00:57:19,227 --> 00:57:20,729
There's 1 more, right?

1143
00:57:21,521 --> 00:57:23,523
Who is it?

1144
00:57:24,024 --> 00:57:25,859
- Who could it be?
- Ah!

1145
00:57:25,942 --> 00:57:28,528
You must know.
This is so annoying.

1146
00:57:29,613 --> 00:57:30,614
Who is it?

1147
00:57:31,698 --> 00:57:33,617
I wonder how they'll react to this person.

1148
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:35,202
How will they react?

1149
00:57:35,285 --> 00:57:38,914
The second Revived Fate Reader,
please come on in.

1150
00:57:42,918 --> 00:57:45,128
Who is it?

1151
00:57:46,171 --> 00:57:48,131
Gosh, please.

1152
00:57:54,513 --> 00:57:56,723
Who is it? Drum roll.

1153
00:57:57,891 --> 00:57:59,685
Oh! Oh! Who is it?

1154
00:58:01,645 --> 00:58:03,647
What? Oh!

1155
00:58:03,730 --> 00:58:05,190
Huh?

1156
00:58:05,273 --> 00:58:07,442
Wow, totally unexpected.

1157
00:59:01,913 --> 00:59:03,915
Translated by Jennifer Jean Lim
